{"number":57810,"title":"[BUG] Azure Storage Share Client doesn&#39;t allow actions on root directory","body":"### Library name and version

Azure.Storage.Files.Shares

### Describe the bug

Whenever a share client is instantiated and root directory client is consumed from it, you&#39;re not allowed to use SetHttpHeadersAsync on that root directory.

### Expected behavior

SetHttpHeadersAsync on root directory client should act normally.

### Actual behavior

SetHttpHeadersAsync throws 404 whenever the root directory client is used.

### Reproduction Steps

Code snipped provided below
```
        var shareClient = new ShareClient(connectionString, &#34;test&#34;);
        var permissionInfo = await shareClient.CreatePermissionAsync(
            new ShareFilePermission { Permission = &#34;any-valid-sddl string&#34;});

        var permissionKey = permissionInfo.Value.FilePermissionKey;
        var rootDirectoryClient  = shareClient.GetRootDirectoryClient();

        await rootDirectoryClient .SetHttpHeadersAsync(
            new FileSmbProperties()
            {
                FilePermissionKey = permissionKey,
            },
            null, CancellationToken.None);
```


### Environment

